ObjectStates.Name: Bag
ObjectStates.Description: This Magic Bag can be used to randomize many things. It even shuffles itself whenever you add or remove items from the bag, so you can use it to randomize turn order as well! :) Ignore or re-roll any dice. Draw them out in turn order. Roll them all at once. Clone them. Make bizarre combinations. Do whatever you want! (The ALL Slug die, I use when deciding turn order as a place holder for something specific I want but that I don't have a die for)
ObjectStates.LuaScript:
function onLoad()
  self.shuffle()
end

size = 0

function update()
   local quantity = self.getQuantity()
   if size ~= quantity then
      size = quantity
      self.shuffle()
   end
end

ObjectStates.Name: Custom_Model_Bag
ObjectStates.Description: The Ruins contained in this bag are ALSO the Ruin Items. Just shuffle/shake the bag and place them at random on the map. If the VB ever Explores a ruin, remove it and press the "2" key to reveal the item found. "1" will revert the Item back to a Ruin. No more need for BLINDFOLD!
